<section class="pg-section" data-section="What To Expect During Your 60-Minute Lymph Drainage Experience">
  <h2 class="pg-h">What To Expect During Your 60-Minute Lymph Drainage Experience</h2>
  <p class="pg-text">Every step is designed for your comfort and results. Here's exactly what happens during your 60-minute treatment at our Millburn spa.</p>
  <p class="pg-text">Consultation &amp; Assessment (5-10 minutes)</p>
  <p class="pg-text">Your treatment begins with a thorough consultation to understand your specific concerns and goals. Our expert esthetician analyzes your lymphatic circulation patterns and creates a customized treatment plan just for you.</p>
  <p class="pg-text">Skin Preparation &amp; Cleansing (10-15 minutes)</p>
  <p class="pg-text">Your skin is gently cleansed to remove makeup, oils, and impurities. We prepare your skin by applying a light massage oil that allows our hands to glide smoothly during the drainage process without any pulling or discomfort.</p>
  <p class="pg-text">Manual Lymph Drainage Massage (35-40 minutes)</p>
  <p class="pg-text">Using gentle, rhythmic pressure and specific hand movements, we guide accumulated fluid from your face toward your lymph nodes. This painless process feels like the most relaxing facial massage as we work around your eyes, jawline, and neck area.</p>
  <p class="pg-text">Finishing Treatment &amp; Aftercare (5-10 minutes)</p>
  <p class="pg-text">We complete your treatment with gentle finishing touches and apply a light moisturizer to protect your freshly treated skin. You'll receive personalized aftercare instructions to maximize your results and maintain that refreshed, sculpted look.</p>
  <a class="pg-btn" href="/manual-lymph-facials">Schedule Now</a>
